Porsche 356 engine, smaller fan, internal (in shroud) oil cooler, no
thermostat or flaps, they actually have the same fan sped as a VW engine due
to a smaller crank and gen pully. I have never had an overheating problem,
even cruising at 100 mph from OC to Lake Havasu in 100 degree heat. Lucky I
guess.

ronnie

